      "author": "Bolt (DevTech Snake)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Hi, everyone, Hope you had a wonderful <img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/jack_o_lantern.png?v=12\" title=\":jack_o_lantern:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":jack_o_lantern:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Halloween​:jack_o_lantern:<br />\nCurrently, I am developing automations using Monday API.<br />\nAnd I want to download the files which are in the files gallery in the item.<br />\n</p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/e/3/e36e5d4ea0249c7b7b273b58481420fde31ddf58.png\" title=\"Screenshot_24\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/3X/e/3/e36e5d4ea0249c7b7b273b58481420fde31ddf58_2_414x500.png\" alt=\"Screenshot_24\" width=\"414\" height=\"500\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">Screenshot_24</span><span class=\"informations\">675×815 30.3 KB</span></div></a></div><p></p>\n<p>I would appreciate it if someone could help me.<br />\nThanks.</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": 208162,
      "postNumber": 2,
      "createdAt": "2024-11-02T10:38:15.805Z",
      "author": "dvdsmpsn (David @ David Simpson Apps)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Try this to get the <code>public_url</code> of files that are in the gallery:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">{\n  items(ids: \"12345678\") {\n    assets(assets_source: gallery) {\n      id\n      name\n      public_url\n    }\n  }\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Check for further details:</p><aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/2X/7/7bfd2edf3c0259b3048238de3e35866f88305b6b.png\" class=\"site-icon\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\" />\n\n      <a href=\"https://developer.monday.com/api-reference/reference/assets-1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">monday.com Platform API</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"aspect-image\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/4/0/4005563d911b52634489bff44a7c345ce1686d22.png\" class=\"thumbnail\" width=\"358\" height=\"36\" /></div>\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://developer.monday.com/api-reference/reference/assets-1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Assets (files)</a></h3>\n\n  <p>Learn how to read, add, and upload assets using the monday.com platform API</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div></div>\n</aside>\n\n<p>Also, a similar &amp; related question:</p><aside class=\"quote quote-modified\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://sea1.discourse-cdn.com/monday/user_avatar/community.monday.com/dvdsmpsn/48/24829_2.png\" class=\"avatar\" />\n    <a href=\"/#/t/99825\">How do I find the files attached to an item in graphql?</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/developers/8\"><span style=\"--category-badge-color:#00ca72;--category-badge-text-color:#FFFFFF\" class=\"badge-category \"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">monday Apps &amp; Developers</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    I have this item, or rather subitem (with a file attached): \n <a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/e/9/e9eafed0b9fa8b8c9f597d0519994d6b76e7e029.jpeg\" title=\"Screenshot 2024-10-04 at 21.48.34\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">[Screenshot 2024-10-04 at 21.48.34]</a> \nThe file is not in a column, or a status, so I don’t seem to be able to locate it using graphql: \n <a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/1/4/14fc534445eebf0615ecacfef931a09c61492db5.png\" title=\"Screenshot 2024-10-04 at 21.49.00\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">[Screenshot 2024-10-04 at 21.49.00]</a> \n\nHow can I find it with graphql?\nWhere am I going wrong?\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n"
    },
